dictionary
Interface Dictionary<K,V>

Type Parameters:
K - the key type.

All Known Implementing Classes:
BinarySearchTree, ChainingHashTable, LinearProbingHashTable, LogFile, OrderedSearchTable
public interface Dictionary<K,V>

Like map, Dictionary stores key-value pairs(entries). Unlike Map, Dictionary can contain duplicate keys; each key can map to more than one value. Two types of Dictionary can be distinguished: ordered and unordered dictionary.
